Package gov.nasa.gsfc.spdf.ssc

Class FixedThreadQueuePool

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.nasa.gsfc.spdf.ssc.FixedThreadQueuePool
  • public class FixedThreadQueuePool
extends java.lang.Object
    This class represents a ThreadPoolExecutor with a fixed size thread pool and limited queue size. A standard Executors.newFixedThreadPool(int) ExecutorService has an unbounded queue.
    Since:
    2.4.5

      • execute

        public boolean execute​(java.lang.String client,
                       java.lang.Runnable task)
        Determines if this executor will accept a new task and, if so, executes it. The decision to accept a new task depends upon the currently system load average and the number of task already queued for execution.
        Parameters:
        client - identifies the client requesting a new task.
        task - the runnable task.
        Returns:
        true if task is executed, false if system load average is greater than maximum and maximum number of tasks are currently queued.

      • shutdownNow

        public java.util.List<java.lang.Runnable> shutdownNow()
        Attempts to stop all actively executing tasks, halts the processing of waiting tasks, and returns a list of the tasks that were awaiting execution.
        Returns:
        list of tasks that never commenced execution.
        See Also:
        ExecutorService.shutdownNow()
